
Claude API at https://console.anthropic.com/ from Anthropic
Gemini API at https://ai.google.dev/gemini-api from Google

Frontier Language Models

1. Closed-Source Frontier Models
These are proprietary models developed and hosted by leading AI companies:

GPT – by OpenAI, https://chatgpt.com/
Claude – by Anthropic, https://claude.ai/new
Gemini – by Google, https://gemini.google.com/app?hl=en-IN
Command R – by Cohere, https://cohere.com/
Perplexity – by Perplexity AI, https://www.perplexity.ai/

2. Open-Source Frontier Models
These models are open-source and can often be fine-tuned, self-hosted, or run locally:

Llama – by Meta
Mixtral – by Mistral
Qwen – by Alibaba Cloud
Gemma – by Google
Phi – by Microsoft

Ways to Use Language Models

1. Chat Interfaces
    Examples: ChatGPT, Claude Web, Gemini Chat
    Ideal for direct, conversational use

2. Cloud APIs (LLM API Access)
    Useful for integrating models into apps and services:
    Frameworks: LangChain
    Managed AI Cloud Services: Amazon Bedrock, Google Vertex AI, Azure Machine Learning

3. Direct Inference
    Run models locally or in a self-managed environment:
    HuggingFace Transformers
    Ollama for running models locally

